    <note>Cheng(1) Xuan(2) [28932] He became an army officer at the beginning of the Yuan. YS, 163.3829 provides an ancestry identical to that provided for probable elder brother, Yun(3) [28925], in his funerary inscription--i.e., ancestors were Luyang people transported with other powerful families at the time of the Northern Wei (元魏) to current Inner Mongolian territory and this Cheng(1) lineage settled in Dongsheng. Xuan(2)'s son, Silian [28933], has the same generational name as Yun(3)'s son. WDY, 3, p. 1415.</note>
